The paper deals with measurements and analysis of millimeter wave (mmWave) penetration loss in an indoor office environment, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of a wideband sliding correlator channel sounder and horn antennas suggests a focus on signal processing and communication technology (cs.MM), while the characterization of the effect of penetration loss for materials with similar composition indicates a possible application in augmented reality (cs.AR) or materials science (cs.MA).
